e\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rxw1665703034255.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rxw1665703034255.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rxw1665703034255.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rxw1665703034255\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Template\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__template_318243\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Template is a Development Object that provides a blueprint for creating new objects.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__p_d96791e1_d96792e1_d96793e1\">It defines properties and code containers that are copied to a newly-created object. There is no inheritance from the template to an object that was created with the template. The template simply provides a reusable pattern that can be used to quickly define new objects that require that pattern.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__p_d96794e1_d96795e1_d96796e1\">Uniface provides a default set of templates for all its Development Objects. These are made available in the Resource Browser of the applicable editor.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__topic_d64842e1_d64843e1_d64844e1_d64845e1_d64846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d501535e59\">\n                     \n Characteristics\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Characteristics</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\"></th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Object type code:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">—</span>\n</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Main Development Object?</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Part of:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Contains:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Generalization:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Specializations:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Compilation Output:</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rxw1665703034255__table_d10793e1_d10794e1_d10795e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">—</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615770\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615770\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Template Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Template A Template is a Development Object that provides a blueprint for creating new objects. It defines properties and code containers that are copied to a newly-created object. There is no inheritance from the template to an object that was created with the template. The template simply provides a reusable pattern that can be used to quickly define new objects that require that pattern. Uniface provides a default set of templates for all its Development Objects. These are made available in the Resource Browser of the applicable editor. Characteristics Characteristics Object type code: — Main Development Object? Yes Part of: — Contains: — Generalization: — Specializations: — Compilation Output: — Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}